Problem0-1. Let A{i + 5 choose i; i∈Z and 0≤i≤4 and 
B={3i|i∈{1,2,4,5}}
--
f(i) = 5 choose i = 5!/(5-i)!i!
f(0) = 0
f(1) = 5!/(4!1!) = 5
f(2) = 5!/(3!2!) = ((5)(4))/2 = 10
f(3) = 5!/(2!3!) = 10
f(4) = 5!/(1!4!) = 5

A = {1, 6, 11, 11, 6} = {1, 6, 11}
B = {3(1), 3(2), 3(4), 3(5)} =
{3, 6, 12, 15}

Evaluate:
(a) A ∩ B
{6}
(b) |A ∪ B| 
A ∪ B = {1, 6, 11, 3, 12, 15}
|A ∪ B| = 6
(c) |A − B|
A - B = {1, 11}
|A - B| = 2

