Problem 0-3.
Evaluate:
Let A = 600/6 and B = 60 mod 42. Are these statements True or False?
A = 100
B = 18
(a)A≡B (mod2) 
Yes, both 100 and 18 have a remainder of 0 when divided by two
(b)A≡B (mod3)
100-18=82
No, 3 doesnt divide 82
(c)A≡B (mod4)
No, 4 doesnt divide 82

