Problem 0-6. An increasing subarray of an integer array is any consecutive sequence of ar- rayintegerswhosevaluesstrictlyincrease.WritePythonfunctioncount long subarrays(A) which accepts Python Tuple A = (a0, a1, . . . , an−1) of n > 0 positive integers, and returns the number of longest increasing subarrays of A, i.e., the number of increasing subarrays with length at least as large as every other increasing subarray. For example, if A = (1,3,4,2,7,5,6,9,8), your program should return 2 since the maximum length of any increasing subarray of A is three and there are two increasing subarrays with that length: specifically, subarrays (1,3,4) and (5,6,9). You can download a code template containing some test cases from the website.
